                    "description": "<p><strong>A new monotypic genus of Heteromurinae from Chilika lake, Ganjam district of Odisha, India is described. <em>Falcomurus </em>gen. n. is similar to other genera of the subfamily, especially to <em>Heteromurus</em> Wankel, 1860 in presence of antennae with 5 segments, 8 + 8 eyes, Abd. I without macrochaetae. It differs from all other genera of Heteromurinae by the combination of: eyes 8 + 8, Ant. III and Ant. IV annulated, unguis with single paired basal inner teeth, dental base commonly with 1+1 falcate type macrochaetae. <em>Falcomurus chilikaensis</em> sp. n., the type species of the new genus is described. An identification key to the genera of Heteromurini is also provided.</strong></p>",
