                    "description": "<p><strong>A new genus <em>Anokha</em> is described in the subfamily Scelioninae (Hymenoptera: Scelionidae), from India with two new species <em>A. anoojii </em>Rajmohana and Veenakumari<em> </em>and <em>A. nigra </em>Rajmohana. The new genus is distinguished from other Scelioninae, by the following combination of characters: closely placed large, round, setigerous tubercles separated by narrow sinuous furrows on head and mesosoma; posteriorly emarginate mesoscutellum with postero-lateral corners drawn into prominent spines. Both sexes are described and imaged. Affinities with closely resembling genera are discussed.</strong></p>",
