                    "description": "<i>Puliciphora pauxilla</i> (Borgmeier), comb. nov.   <p> <i>Pulicimyia pauxilla</i> Borgmeier, 1960: 339.</p>   <p>In the key to Neotropical <i>Puliciphora</i> females (Disney, 2003 a) this species will readily run to couplet 27, lead 2 to <i>P. imbecilla</i>, as does the new species <i>P. jacquemart <i>i</i> (see above), and is then best distinguished by its possession of small wing rudiments (similar to Fig. 23) and T 6 being represented by its anterior apodemes only.</i></p>",
