                    "description": "<p> <b>Checklist of Oriental species of <i>Parancistrocerus</i> Bequaert</b> </p>   <p>(1) <i>P. acarophilus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Philippines.</p>   <p>(2) <i>P. acclivus</i> Gusenleitner, 2007 &mdash; Laos.</p>   <p>(3a) <i>P. androcles androcles</i> (Meade-Waldo, 1910) &mdash; India: Kerala, Meghalaya, Tripura (new record); Sri Lanka; Myanmar; Thailand; Vietnam; Malaysia (including Sabah); Singapore; Indonesia: Sumatra, Java, Sulawesi; Philippines.</p>   <p>(3b) <i>P. androcles marginalis</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Philippines.</p>   <p>(3c) <i>P. androcles scutellaris</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Philippines.</p>   <p>(3d) <i>P. androcles sulawensis</i> Giordani Soika, 1993 &mdash; Indonesia: Sulawesi.</p>   <p>(3e) <i>P. androcles sumbanus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Indonesia: Sumba.</p>   <p>(4) <i>P. assamensis</i> (Meade-Waldo, 1910) &mdash; India: Meghalaya; Nepal; Myanmar;</p>   <p>Laos; Vietnam.</p>  <p>(5) <i>P. capocacciai</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Myanmar; Laos.</p>   <p>(6) <i>P. citropictus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Indonesia: Sulawesi.</p>   <p>(7) <i>P. cylindricus</i> (de Saussure, 1862) &mdash; Indonesia: Sulawesi.</p>   <p>(8) <i>P. cylindroides</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Indonesia: Sulawesi.</p>   <p>(9a) <i>P. difformis difformis</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Malaysia: Sabah.</p>   <p>(9b) <i>P. difformis nigerrimus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Malaysia: Sabah.</p>   <p>(10) <i>P. feai</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; India: Sikkim; Myanmar; Malaysia.</p>   <p>(11) <i>P. fulvipes fulvipes</i> (de Saussure, 1855) &mdash; U.S.A.; Mexico; Costa Rica; adventive in Midway Island.</p>   <p>(12) <i>P. gracilior</i> Giordani Soika, 1995 &mdash; Indonesia: Sulawesi.</p>   <p>(13) <i>P. holzschuhi</i> Gusenleitner, 1987 &mdash; India (new record): Arunachal Pradesh, Meghalaya; Nepal.</p>   <p>(14) <i>P. hongkongensis</i> Gusenleitner, 2002 &mdash; China: Hong Kong.</p>   <p>(15a) <i>P. incorruptus demens</i> Giordani Soika, 1972 &mdash; India: Sikkim.</p>   <p>(15b) <i>P. incorruptus incorruptus</i> Giordani Soika, 1972 &mdash; India: Assam.</p>   <p>(15c) <i>P. incorruptus kalimpongensis</i> Giordani</p>   <p>Soika, 1994 &mdash; India: West Bengal.</p>  <p>(16) <i>P. inflaticeps</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Indonesia: Java.</p>   <p>(17) <i>P. insolitus</i> Gusenleitner, 2012 &mdash; Vietnam.</p>   <p>(18) <i>P. intermediatus</i> (Sonan, 1939), NEW COMBINATION &mdash; Taiwan.</p>   <p>(19) <i>P. irritatus</i> Giordani Soika, 1972 &mdash; India: Sikkim.</p>   <p>(20) <i>P. jaferpaloti</i> Girish Kumar &amp; Carpenter <b>sp. n.</b> &mdash; India: Kerala.</p>   <p>(21) <i>P. kennethianus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Malaysia: Sabah.</p>   <p>(22) <i>P. kolambuganensis</i> (von Schulthess, 1934) &mdash; Philippines.</p>   <p>(23) <i>P. kuraruensis</i> (Sonan, 1939), NEW COMBINATION &mdash; Taiwan.</p>   <p>(24) <i>P. loharbandensis</i> Girish Kumar &amp; Carpenter <b>sp. n.</b> &mdash; India: Assam.</p>   <p>(25) <i>P. luzonicola</i> van der Vecht, 1981 &mdash; Philippines.</p>   <p>(26) <i>P. makilingi</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Philippines.</p>   <p>(27) <i>P. malayanus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Malaysia.</p>   <p>(28) <i>P. nigriventris</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Malaysia: Sabah.</p>   <p>(29) <i>P. nitobei</i> (Sonan, 1939), NEW COMBINATION &mdash; Taiwan.</p>   <p>(30) <i>P. pseudodynerus</i> (Dalla Torre, 1889)&mdash; Indonesia: Java.</p>   <p>(31) <i>P. pseudallodynerus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Malaysia: Sabah.</p>   <p>(32) <i>P. reflexus</i> Gusenleitner, 2011 &mdash; Laos.</p>   <p>(33) <i>P. rhipheus</i> (Cameron, 1904) &mdash; India: West Bengal; Laos.</p>   <p>(34a) <i>P. robertianus javanus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Indonesia: Java.</p>   <p>(34b) <i>P. robertianus palawanensis</i> Giordani Soika, 1993 &mdash; Philippines.</p>   <p>(34c) <i>P. robertianus robertianus</i> (Cameron, 1903) &mdash; Malaysia: Sarawak; Indonesia: Sumatra.</p>   <p>(35) <i>P. samarensis</i> (von Schulthess, 1934) &mdash; Laos; Philippines.</p>   <p>(36) <i>P. siamensis</i> Gusenleitner, 2003 &mdash; Thailand.</p>   <p>(37) <i>P. simoni</i> Gusenleitner, 2013 &mdash; Laos.</p>   <p>(38) <i>P. sulcatus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Thailand; Laos.</p>   <p>(39) <i>P. taihorinensis</i> (von Schulthess, 1934) &mdash; Taiwan.</p>   <p>(40) <i>P. taihorinshoensis</i> (von Schulthess, 1934) &mdash; Taiwan.</p>   <p>(41) <i>P. taikonus</i> (Sonan, 1939), NEW COMBINATION &mdash; Taiwan.</p>   <p>(42a) <i>P. triconcavus rufipes</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Indonesia: Sumba.</p>   <p>(42b) <i>P. triconcavus triconcavus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Indonesia: Sulawesi.</p>   <p>(43) <i>P. turensis</i> Girish Kumar &amp; Carpenter <b>sp. n.</b> &mdash; India: Meghalaya.</p>   <p>(44) <i>P. vicinus</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; India: Kerala (new record), Maharashtra.</p>   <p>(45a) <i>P. yachowensis konkunesis</i> Giordani Soika, 1994 &mdash; Taiwan.</p>   <p>(45b) <i>P. yachowensis yachowensis</i> Giordani Soika, 1986 &mdash; China; Laos.</p>   <p>(46) <i>P. yamanei</i> Gusenleitner, 2000 &mdash; Taiwan.</p>",
