                    "description": "<p> <b>Key to the species of <i>Romblonella</i>, based on the worker caste</b> </p>   <p>1 In profile, petiole longer than tall, relatively flat dorsally, without a round dorsal outline &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.... <b> <i>R. palauensis</i> Smith, 1953</b> (Palau Islands)</p>   <p>- In profile, petiole taller than long, with a round dorsal outline.....&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;&hellip;...&hellip;&hellip; 2</p>  <p>2 In full-face view, dorsum of head longitudinally carinate&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. 3</p>  <p>- In full-face view, dorsum of head reticulate&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;... 6</p>  <p>3 Dorsum of head with interrupted longitudinal carinae&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;&hellip;.. <b> <i>R</i>. <i>heatwolei</i> Taylor, 1991</b> (Australia)</p>   <p>- Dorsum of head with longitudinal carinae that extend from posterior margin of clypeus to posterior margin of head&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. 4</p>  <p>4 Mesosoma, petiole and postpetiole dorsally longitudinally carinate &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; <b> <i>R. yapensis</i> Smith, 1953</b> (Micronesia: Caroline Islands)</p>   <p>- Mesosoma, petiole and postpetiole dorsally reticulate&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;... 5</p>  <p>5 In full-face view, sides of head diverging posteriorly; frontal carinae longer, almost reaching posterior margin of head; posteromedian clypeus as wide as frontal lobe&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; <i>R</i>. <i>longinoi</i> <b>sp. n.</b> (Mamutik I., Borneo)</p>   <p>- In full-face view, sides of head subparallel; frontal carinae shorter, more than one eyelength from posterior margin of head; posteromedian clypeus wider than frontal lobe..................&hellip;&hellip; <b> <i>R. townesi</i> Smith, 1953</b> (Marianas Islands)</p>   <p>6 Dorsum of first gastral tergite longitudinally costulate with interstitial punctulae; in fullface view, head subrectangular (CI 84-89); median clypeus narrow, only as wide as frontal lobe&hellip;.....&hellip; <b> <i>R. coryae</i> General, 2015</b> (Palawan I., Philippines)</p>   <p>- Dorsum of first gastral tergite smooth, punctulate or reticulate but never longitudinally costulate; in full-face view, head subquadrate (CI&gt; 94); median clypeus wider than frontal lobe&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..... 7</p>  <p>7 Dorsum of first gastral tergite smooth &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. <b> <i>R. liogaster</i> (Santschi, 1928)</b> (Fiji I.)</p>   <p>- Dorsum of first gastral tergite finely punctulate or reticulate, but never smooth.......................................................... 8</p>  <p>8 Dorsum of mesosoma longitudinally carinate, with scattered cross-hatches; median clypeus without well-developed median carina........................... <b> <i>R. scrobifera</i> (Emery, 1897)</b> (New Guinea)</p>   <p>- Dorsum of mesosoma reticulate; median clypeus with well-developed median carina&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; 9</p>  <p>9 In dorsal view, propodeal spines divergent throughout their entire length; body concolorous yellow&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. <b> <i>R. elysii</i> (Mann, 1919)</b> (Solomon Islands)</p>   <p>- In dorsal view, propodeal spines basally divergent but distal half parallel or curved slightly inward; body dark-brown with lighter appendages...&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; <b> <i>R. opaca</i> (F. Smith, 1861)</b> (Indonesia, Philippines)</p>",
